# 1. Overview

The Inter-Scalar Coherence Engine (ISC Engine) is a hybrid neural–symbolic system that evaluates the **structural coherence** 
of any text.

It determines whether a passage:
- preserves internal proportionality,
- maintains directional consistency (Direction-of-Meaning),
- avoids structural drift or simulacrum,
- exhibits mechanism-based reasoning instead of rhetorical surface,
- remains anchored to an internal return/feedback loop.

This system does **not** classify sentiment, ideology, or topic;  
it evaluates **structure**, not content.

